<subsection xml:id="subsec-determining-trigonometric-ratios-of-acute-angles-using-calculators">
    <title>Determining Trigonometric Ratios of Acute Angles Using Calculators</title>
    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Work in pairs}</m>
            </p>

            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Use a scientific calculator to find the values of the following trigonometric ratios for the given angles. 
                            Ensure your calculator is set to degrees mode.
                        </p>

                        <tabular top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                            <row header="yes">
                                <cell>Angle<m> \theta</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>\sin \theta</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>\cos \theta</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>\tan \theta</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>15^\circ</m></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                            </row>

                            <row>
                                <cell><m>30^\circ</m></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                            </row>

                            <row>
                                <cell><m>45^\circ</m></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>60^\circ</m></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                            </row>

                            <row>
                                <cell><m>75^\circ</m></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                            </row>

                            <row>
                                <cell><m>90^\circ</m></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                                <cell></cell>
                            </row>
                        </tabular>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Follow the steps below to determine the value of <m>\sin 30^\circ</m>.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            (i) Press the <m>\sin</m> button on your calculator.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            (ii) Enter the angle <m>30</m> using the number keys.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            (iii) Press the <m>(=)</m> button to calculate the value.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Follow the same steps to find all other trigonometric ratios in the table.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Share your results with the class and compare the values you obtained.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </activity>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Calculate the value of each of the following using your calculator, giving your answers correct to 4 significant figures:
            </p>

            <sidebyside>
                <p>
                  (a)  <m>\sin 25^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    (b)  <m>\tan 50^\circ </m>
                </p>

                <p>
                     (c)  <m>\cos 70^\circ</m>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </statement>

        <solution>
            <p>
                (a)  <m>\sin 25^\circ </m>
            </p>

            <p>
                press the <m>\sin</m> button, enter <m>25</m>, and then press <m>(=)</m>. The calculator displays: <m>0.42261826</m>
            </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the value of <m>\sin 25^\circ</m> is <m>0.4226</m>.
                </p>

                <p>
                    (b)  <m>\tan 50^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    press the <m>\tan</m> button, enter <m>50</m>, and then press <m>(=)</m>. The calculator displays: <m> 1.19175359</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the value of <m>\tan 50^\circ</m> is <m>1.1918</m>.
                </p>

                <p>
                    (c)  <m>\cos 70^\circ</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    press the <m>\cos</m> button, enter <m>70</m>, and then press <m>(=)</m>. The calculator displays: <m>0.34202014</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the value of <m>\cos 70^\circ</m> is <m>0.3420</m>.
                </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Use a calculator to find the angle whose sine is <m>0.8660</m>
            </p>
        </statement>

        <solution>
            <p>
               (i) press the shift key followed by the sin key to get sin⁻¹.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                (ii) enter <m>0.8660</m> and press the <m>(=)</m> button. The calculator displays: <m>60</m>
            </p>    

            <p>
                Therefore, the angle whose sine is <m>0.8660</m> is <m>60^\circ</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    
</subsection>